# What is Networking? (TryHackMe)

## Overview
This lab introduced the basic concept of computer networking and how devices communicate with each other over networks.

## What I learned
- What networking is and why it is important
- The difference between local networks and the internet
- How devices are identified on a network
- Basic understanding of ICMP and ping

## Tools used
- TryHackMe guided lab environment
- Ping (ICMP)

## What I practiced
- Identifying devices on a network
- Using ping to test connectivity between devices
- Understanding how data travels across networks

## Why this matters
Networking knowledge is essential in cybersecurity because understanding how systems communicate helps with detecting issues, troubleshooting, and securing networks.
